summary: The Echoes of Stories Never Told
title: The Echoes of Stories Never Told
body:
Author: copperbadge

Fandom: Game Of Thrones

Rating: Teen

Words: 6,011

Summary: Gendry looks out for all the kids who come to his foster home, but Arya is different right from the start.

Link: https://archiveofourown.org/works/2283096

Review: This was less about them being in a foster home together, and more about their relationship which started in a foster home. I really liked the development, the dedication they showed to each other, and how to story moved with them from the foster home.

summary: The first time I watched GoT season 7 I thought it was cool. I didn't understand why people were talking bad about it. But then...
body:
The first time I watched GoT season 7 I thought it was cool. I didn’t understand why people were talking bad about it. But then I read the books, and now I re-watched the whole season and honestly…


GoT season 7 - A quick summary:

- grrrrreat opening

- boring stuff

- boring stuff

- super cool Daenerys-finally-going-home scene

- boring stuff

- super cool Olenna’s death

- boring stuff

- super cool first encounter between Jon and Daenerys

- boring stuff

- wait, why is Arya acting like this? I used to like this little creep!

- boring stuff

- boring stuff

- one of the last decent human beings on this planet, now totally f****d up by a very bad internship. Relatable.

- boring stuff

- very cool ice zombie dragon

- boring stuff

- Jamie finally saying goodbye to that monster-of-a-twin-lover, yay!

- boring stuff

- wow, Jon is the rightful heir to the Iron Throne, but we already got it like seven episodes ago.

- a little incest
